modified how measure to lily method works due to how it needs to be notated - i.e each measure can't have it's own staff created or it will be outputted in lilypond as 1 part with about 30 staves to a part

fixed a problem with int and str casting of pitch.octave, needs refactoring so this happens in MxmlParser instead as this is a very hacky fix. Also added a simple run script which loads a given testcase and outputs a .ly file. next step is to find how to run lilypond from inside python without it being a difficult fresh installation on another machine
updated simple script so it now works and does output of pdf file to appropriate folder, needs testing on other testcases

added tests and a class for calling a lilypond string, outputting it to an ly file and running it from python. Currently just checks that lilypond hasn't thrown chunks by checking whether a PDF has been created successfully.

Fixed text output to lilypond so that if the text field is empty or full of spaces nothing is output. Also fixed a duplication error. need to refactor how certain elements are collected in measure class, as lilypond dynamics have to come attached to a particular note, so strings like "e''2 \direction \dynamic \stemDown will throw chunks.

added a new test to the lilypond tests, which takes the lilypond output and runs it in lilypond to test whether the syntax itself is valid lilypond. Also modified lilypond render to take wrapper strings, which mean that singular notes can be put in the right mode for compilation to confirm that any syntax errors in the aforementioned tests are not because lilypond is missing elements which would be added to the string by the measure class.
fixed up most of the note compilation errors. Still to do tremolos, then move on to measures which will be more tricky
finished up fixes for notation classes.
added compilation tests to testMeasure lilypond methods

complete refactor of adding directions/expressions/notes to measures: these are all now separated into different dictionaries. The first two are indexed first by the staff id, then by the last note found in that staff. notes is only indexed by the staff it is in which then gives a list of notes.
closer to getting all of them to compile, visual checks still necessary - would like to have a way to incorporate these into unit tests using developer input (i.e "does it look right? y/n")
implemented clef and key toLilys in measure which I missed. need to add unit tests for both to measure lilytests.

lines testcase now passing, need to work on bracketed bars as at the moment they're ignored while I figure out how they work.

all lilypond compilation tests work now, however tremolo notation is wrong. - in general, value needs calculating based on the value of the note. In the case that it is a start or stop tremolo, the value comes from the total value of each note in the tremolo. - as a result, need to figure out how to do this as it will probably need to be on a measure level annoyingly.

mega refactor to Note class.
